22/04/2003
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- A two-day meeting of justice and interior ministers from the Balkans began Tuesday (22 April) in Thessaloniki. 
Participants are to discuss the Stabilisation and Association Process, regional co-operation, border protection and common efforts to fight organised crime, drugs, human and arms trafficking. 
(BTA, Turkish Daily News - 22/04/03; MIA, ANA - 21/04/03)
